ENTRY       EC 5.5.1.18                 Enzyme
NAME        lycopene epsilon-cyclase;
            CrtL-e;
            LCYe
CLASS       Isomerases;
            Intramolecular lyases;
            Intramolecular lyases (only sub-subclass identified to date)
SYSNAME     carotenoid psi-end group lyase (decyclizing)
REACTION    carotenoid psi-end group = carotenoid epsilon-end group
ALL_REAC    (other) R06960 R06963 R07840
SUBSTRATE   carotenoid psi-end group
PRODUCT     carotenoid epsilon-end group
COMMENT     The carotenoid lycopene has the psi-end group at both ends. When acting on one end, this enzyme forms delta-carotene. When acting on both ends, it forms epsilon-carotene.
